# Nursy AI Component And Phase Plan

## Architecture Rule

```text
Mobile-first, offline-first, cloud-enhanced.
```

The Android app is the product. Room DB is the local source of truth. AWS is a backup/sync/recovery layer. Cloud AI is optional and used only for occasional premium reports.

## Current Components

- `apps/mobile`: Android app with Compose, Room, WorkManager, local rules, notifications, and sync.
- `infra/dynamodb`: DynamoDB table definition for synced records.
- `skills`: repo-local implementation guidance.

## Component Map

### 1. Mobile App Shell

Jetpack Compose navigation, app scaffold, bottom navigation, dashboard entry, and emergency card access.

### 2. Authentication And Profile

User identity, profile fields, health profile, emergency contacts, and local profile persistence. Cloud auth should be Cognito when implemented.

### 3. Daily Health Check-In

Mood, energy, sleep, stress, water intake, notes, and date-based local history.

### 4. Symptom Tracking

Symptom name, severity, duration, notes, active/resolved state, and history.

### 5. Medication Management

Medication records, dose events, taken/missed status, adherence score, and reminder scheduling.

### 6. Health Dashboard

Local health score, today's summary, active symptoms, medications, local insights, and sync status.

### 7. Health Timeline

Chronological local history built from check-ins, symptoms, medications, dose events, and insights.

### 8. AI Symptom Journal

Natural-language note parser that extracts structured symptoms locally and asks for confirmation before saving.

### 9. Local AI Health Insights

Deterministic offline rules for repeated symptoms, low sleep, fatigue, hydration, stress, and severity warnings.

### 10. Emergency Health Card

Offline display of name, blood type, allergies, chronic conditions, and emergency contacts.

### 11. Notifications

Medication, check-in, hydration, and appointment reminders.

### 12. Offline Storage

Room entities, DAO queries, local migrations, and sync metadata.

### 13. Sync Engine

WorkManager queue, API client, retry behavior, conflict metadata, and DynamoDB payload mapping.

### 14. Cloud Backend

Cognito auth, API Gateway/Lambda sync endpoints, DynamoDB persistence, recovery reads, and optional cloud AI entry points.

## Phase Plan

1. Foundation and Room data model
2. Core mobile offline experience
3. Local rules and AI symptom journal
4. Notifications and reminders
5. Sync and cloud persistence
6. Optional cloud AI reports
7. Polish, testing, and mobile demo readiness

## Guardrails

- Never block local health tracking on network access.
- Keep all health wording in the tracking companion category: summarize symptoms and patterns, never diagnose, predict disease, prescribe treatment, or replace doctor advice.
- Prefer safe phrasing such as "This is a pattern worth reviewing with a doctor", "You might want to mention this at your next appointment", "Here is a summary of your symptoms", and "No diagnosis is provided, only tracking insights".
- Do not send sensitive free-text notes to cloud AI by default.
- Mark records synced only after confirmed backend persistence.
- Keep cloud report prompts short and structured.
- Avoid AWS services with always-on cost during the credit period.
